      • GeoJsonElement

        public GeoJsonElement(com.github.filosganga.geogson.model.Feature feature,
                      java.lang.String[] idKeys)
        Creates a GeoJsonElement from the given Feature identified by the given properties.
        Depending on the value of idKeys the uid will be one of the following:
        • if idKeys == null, then the standard GeoJSON uid will be used
        • if idKeys.length == 0, then all properties will be used as the uid
        • if idKeys.length > 0, then the given properties will be used as the uid
        A uid is considered invalid if
        • the Feature doesn't have the standard GeoJSON "id" key
        • at least one of the given properties doesn't exist
        Parameters:
        feature - the feature
        idKeys - a list of properties to use as an identifier
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the id given is invalid
